1
00:00:02,603 --> 00:00:05,539
The female chromosome is XX.

2
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:06,874
Good morning.

3
00:00:06,941 --> 00:00:10,244
The male chromosome is XY.

4
00:00:10,311 --> 00:00:13,514
However, this past half-century,

5
00:00:13,581 --> 00:00:17,351
it is said that the Y chromosome
is deteriorating worldwide.

6
00:00:18,719 --> 00:00:23,157
In other words, male power is declining.

7
00:00:23,858 --> 00:00:28,796
Long-time male-dominated Teiko Real Estate

8
00:00:28,863 --> 00:00:33,534
was about to start a drastic reform.

9
00:00:34,368 --> 00:00:36,337
As you may all know,

10
00:00:36,570 --> 00:00:40,741
Sangenya will be participating
in the "Woman Project".

11
00:00:41,142 --> 00:00:42,777
What's the "Woman Project"?

12
00:00:43,244 --> 00:00:46,280
-You didn't read the mass e-mail?
-No, I didn't.

13
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:50,785
To expand the opportunity
for women to shine at a work place,

14
00:00:50,851 --> 00:00:54,622
the headquarters started
this project for women, by women.

15
00:00:54,688 --> 00:00:57,858
The real estate industry
still seems male dominated,

16
00:00:58,192 --> 00:01:00,995
so the company wants to appeal
to women's success.

17
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:03,597
-Does it mean a flashy employee?
-Flashy?

18
00:01:04,365 --> 00:01:05,866
It means good-looking.

19
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:08,903
I have never sold a house with my face.

20
00:01:09,203 --> 00:01:10,304
It's not what that means.

21
00:01:11,105 --> 00:01:15,409
Sangenya, please hold back
your regular sales to do this project.

22
00:01:15,876 --> 00:01:17,912
And you need to stick
to regular working hours.

23
00:01:18,279 --> 00:01:21,916
Manager! My job is to sell properties!

24
00:01:22,416 --> 00:01:25,586
This project will lead to selling
more properties too, of course.

25
00:01:25,853 --> 00:01:27,822
So, even if you don't
sell properties like before,

26
00:01:27,888 --> 00:01:29,757
your evaluation won't change.

27
00:01:29,824 --> 00:01:33,127
I don't sell properties for my evaluation!

28
00:01:33,194 --> 00:01:38,532
That may be, but your idea of just
simply selling properties is questionable.

29
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:42,403
Then I'll take part in this project,
and I will still sell properties too!

30
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:48,042
Then that's fine, but do not go around
selling properties all night long!

31
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:51,946
Come home early once in a while
to get some rest.

32
00:01:52,213 --> 00:01:54,114
He's talking about his private life.

33
00:01:54,181 --> 00:01:55,516
They should do that at home.

34
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:59,753
This is an order as Sangenya's boss.

35
00:02:01,055 --> 00:02:03,891
The morning meeting
is now over! Dismissed!

36
00:02:10,664 --> 00:02:11,565
Adachi!

37
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:14,134
What's the matter?
You don't look so perky lately.

38
00:02:15,736 --> 00:02:19,740
You used to have those Adachi fan club
ladies around your fingers before.

39
00:02:20,407 --> 00:02:22,510
I may be in a slump right now.

40
00:02:23,077 --> 00:02:24,545
What? You mean this?

41
00:02:25,579 --> 00:02:27,882
No, it's just a slump.

42
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:34,622
There's a daycare for your sons
and a market on your way to the station,

43
00:02:34,955 --> 00:02:37,191
and there's a big park
in the neighborhood too.

44
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:39,093
Please, go ahead.

45
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:43,564
It'll be great if I can leave them
at daycare on my way to the station.

46
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:47,568
The entrance area is huge, so please
leave your stroller here.

47
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:49,603
No way!

48
00:02:50,538 --> 00:02:54,074
Oh, it even has a little sink here.
This is handy!

49
00:02:54,308 --> 00:02:58,746
They always come home in
muddy shoes, so this is so helpful.

50
00:02:59,146 --> 00:03:02,683
Mr. Rusudo,
how did you know what I wanted?

51
00:03:03,217 --> 00:03:04,285
I'm a realtor.

52
00:03:05,819 --> 00:03:09,523
Over here, the stairs have a safety
net on the railing

53
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:11,392
to prevent children from falling.

54
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:13,360
We care about safety.

55
00:03:13,427 --> 00:03:15,496
Care!

56
00:03:16,163 --> 00:03:18,799
Oh, even for the kitchen!

57
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:23,637
I was worried about kids getting
close to the stove, so it's helpful!

58
00:03:23,704 --> 00:03:28,242
It's amazing how you manage both
the home and raise your kids.

59
00:03:28,742 --> 00:03:32,846
I'm so glad I had Adachi refer
me to you, Mr. Rusudo.

60
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:35,649
You and Adachi started
working at the same time?

61
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,819
You work at Teiko Real Estate,

62
00:03:39,153 --> 00:03:41,889
yet was it okay for me to be your agent?

63
00:03:42,823 --> 00:03:45,726
If I ask my co-workers, I feel bad
demanding so many things,

64
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:49,163
and I don't want things to get awkward
when I don't like a place.

65
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:53,000
Plus, Mr. Rusudo, you are very capable.

66
00:03:53,767 --> 00:03:55,169
Thank you very much.

67
00:03:56,737 --> 00:04:00,374
Excuse me, are you looking
to move into this place?

68
00:04:01,075 --> 00:04:04,044
I'm a realtor. We were here for a viewing.

69
00:04:04,678 --> 00:04:08,849
I live downstairs.
This condo is well-built,

70
00:04:09,149 --> 00:04:12,353
but if people are jumping up and down
like they were doing just now, it's loud.

71
00:04:13,153 --> 00:04:15,022
I'm sorry about being inconsiderate.

72
00:04:15,856 --> 00:04:20,294
They have great cushioning
materials now, so I'll think of something.

73
00:04:20,561 --> 00:04:25,032
I work at home,
so loud noises are a nuisance.

74
00:04:28,936 --> 00:04:31,205
I'm sorry if it made you feel bad.

75
00:04:31,538 --> 00:04:34,942
Did he get mad
because I jumped up and down?

76
00:04:35,976 --> 00:04:37,945
No, it's fine.

77
00:04:38,812 --> 00:04:43,117
I'll find a home
that's okay for you jump up and down.

78
00:04:43,417 --> 00:04:44,852
Thank you.

79
00:04:46,654 --> 00:04:47,755
Leave it to me.

80
00:04:49,390 --> 00:04:50,324
Hello.

81
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:54,528
Asakura, you look well as always.

82
00:04:55,095 --> 00:04:57,631
Did you get younger
after getting remarried?

83
00:04:57,698 --> 00:04:58,899
You think so?

84
00:04:58,966 --> 00:05:01,835
Asakura, you haven't changed a bit.

85
00:05:02,069 --> 00:05:04,104
Mr. Fuse! It's been a while!

86
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:06,640
What? Is it time for the Yashiro
and Asakura duo to return?

87
00:05:06,707 --> 00:05:10,744
No, Asakura is the foundation of
planning and development,

88
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:13,013
even if sales begged her
to come back, she won't.

89
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,782
Oh, this brings back memories.

90
00:05:15,182 --> 00:05:18,052
Those days when I sold properties
with you all day long.

91
00:05:18,686 --> 00:05:21,488
Back then I spent more time with you
than with my boyfriend.

92
00:05:21,722 --> 00:05:22,856
Right.

93
00:05:23,290 --> 00:05:26,326
Manager, that strangely
shaped property in Suginami is sold.

94
00:05:26,894 --> 00:05:29,830
I sold it for ¥35 million.

95
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:31,932
Good job.

96
00:05:32,366 --> 00:05:34,201
I don't mean to intrude, but who is she?

97
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,671
She is Asakura
from planning and development.

98
00:05:37,738 --> 00:05:39,239
You'll work with her
for the Woman Project.

99
00:05:39,773 --> 00:05:41,809
She used to be in sales
and worked under me.

100
00:05:42,276 --> 00:05:44,678
I'm Asakura, nice to meet you.

101
00:05:44,745 --> 00:05:47,915
I'm Sangenya. Nice to meet you.

102
00:05:49,116 --> 00:05:54,321
Focus on work. Focus on work.
Focus on work.

103
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:57,925
Adachi!

104
00:06:00,294 --> 00:06:01,428
Usami!

105
00:06:01,495 --> 00:06:03,964
I have a meeting for
that Woman Project now.

106
00:06:05,132 --> 00:06:06,166
Oh, how's the house hunting?

107
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:11,905
Mr. Rusudo is searching for
a kid-friendly home. It's so helpful!

108
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:14,575
Well, I really wanted to sell it,

109
00:06:15,075 --> 00:06:17,678
but I get how it's hard to talk
to your co-worker about a house.

110
00:06:19,113 --> 00:06:21,181
Oh, Mr. Rusudo was praising you, Adachi.

111
00:06:21,749 --> 00:06:24,885
Um… He said you are cute like Bambi!

112
00:06:26,353 --> 00:06:27,387
Bambi?

113
00:06:28,956 --> 00:06:30,691
I'm Asakura from planning and development.

114
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:34,128
Hello! I'm Usami from
the Internet Advancement department.

115
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:39,266
I'm Sangenya, a chief at the Shinjuku
real estate brokerage division.

116
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,401
This is my assistant, Niwano.

117
00:06:41,468 --> 00:06:43,804
I'm Niwano. Nice to meet you.

118
00:06:44,304 --> 00:06:46,140
I'm so honored to work
with you, Ms. Sangenya,

119
00:06:46,206 --> 00:06:49,910
the genius realtor,
and the jewel of Teiko Real Estate,

120
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:54,047
Ms. Sangenya,
you have a famous saying, right?

121
00:06:54,114 --> 00:06:56,016
I want to hear that too.

122
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:57,785
Please wait one second.

123
00:06:58,152 --> 00:07:00,954
That's something that comes out naturally
when she's selling properties.

124
00:07:01,021 --> 00:07:02,456
I think it's fine. It'll be a booster!

125
00:07:02,823 --> 00:07:03,724
A booster?

126
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:04,825
I want to hear it!

127
00:07:05,325 --> 00:07:07,528
-Well, then as a booster!
-What?

128
00:07:07,828 --> 00:07:10,898
There is no property I can't sell!

129
00:07:31,585 --> 00:07:34,354
I strongly felt during my years in sales
that women's input

130
00:07:34,588 --> 00:07:36,790
usually becomes a deciding factor.

131
00:07:37,191 --> 00:07:39,092
So I want this smartphone portal site

132
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,995
to be appealing to women.

133
00:07:42,062 --> 00:07:45,465
We want its design to be cute, right?

134
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:50,470
Don't you think this is cute?

135
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:53,674
What is this?

136
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,676
This is my blog.

137
00:07:55,943 --> 00:07:58,879
It's quite popular among
moms raising their kids.

138
00:07:59,112 --> 00:08:02,115
Our clients are families,

139
00:08:02,182 --> 00:08:06,119
so I think we should choose something
that will appeal to mothers with kids.

140
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:10,190
When you say "family" do
you only mean families with kids?

141
00:08:11,191 --> 00:08:15,295
I don't like kids,
so I don't plan to have them,

142
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:17,698
but I consider
my husband and I as a family.

143
00:08:17,931 --> 00:08:19,533
Ah, I'm sorry…

144
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:26,974
But if our aim is the general public,
then childrearing is a popular topic.

145
00:08:27,741 --> 00:08:29,176
What do you think, Ms. Sangenya?

146
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:31,511
Even if it's a woman or a man,

147
00:08:31,578 --> 00:08:36,650
or whether they have kids or not,
I don't categorize my clients.

148
00:08:36,917 --> 00:08:40,687
However, in general,
men care about the property value,

149
00:08:40,954 --> 00:08:43,624
and women care more about
the practical side,

150
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:46,526
like the sunlight,
facilities, colors and storage.

151
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:48,629
I see.

152
00:08:50,063 --> 00:08:51,265
Asakura is that

153
00:08:51,331 --> 00:08:55,269
capable person who took part in branding
Teiko Real Estate condos, right?

154
00:08:55,602 --> 00:08:56,503
Right.

155
00:08:56,570 --> 00:09:00,641
She was so capable she probably
can't get married.

156
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:03,176
-Asakura is married.
-What?

157
00:09:03,243 --> 00:09:06,213
I attended her wedding.
Her husband seemed really nice.

158
00:09:06,446 --> 00:09:08,949
So she's using her maiden name for work?

159
00:09:09,249 --> 00:09:12,853
The wife who still uses
her maiden name at work

160
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:16,123
makes it seem like her husband is
the weaker one, right?

161
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:19,693
Mr. Fuse, are you referring to me…

162
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:22,496
There was one so close to us.

163
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:25,899
A workplace that bashes
competent women is not cool.

164
00:09:26,199 --> 00:09:28,268
I'm not interested at all.

165
00:09:29,102 --> 00:09:34,107
We should discuss this know-how
early on with the web designers.

166
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:36,810
-I'll see you later.
-What?

167
00:09:37,144 --> 00:09:38,679
Oh, I have reduced working hours.

168
00:09:39,346 --> 00:09:42,482
-We were just warming up.
-I have to go pick up my son.

169
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:43,884
I see.

170
00:09:43,951 --> 00:09:46,887
I'm fine for you two to decide after this.

171
00:09:47,287 --> 00:09:50,357
I'll be in touch
about the next meeting. Okay!

172
00:09:50,624 --> 00:09:51,758
Good bye.

173
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:53,360
Take care.

174
00:09:54,728 --> 00:09:57,297
She should have told us first
about her reduced working hours.

175
00:09:57,597 --> 00:10:02,336
Well, I'm sure it's difficult
to work and raise kids.

176
00:10:02,402 --> 00:10:04,805
Working earnestly is difficult too.

177
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:06,206
You are absolutely right.

178
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:09,609
Don't you feel the same way, Ms. Sangenya?

179
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:13,747
I saw your expression on
your face when she left, so I know.

180
00:10:15,983 --> 00:10:18,852
I'm actually looking
for a house right now.

181
00:10:19,186 --> 00:10:20,887
Could you help us out, Ms. Sangenya?

182
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:25,058
My job is to sell properties.
Please leave it to me!

183
00:10:25,959 --> 00:10:28,562
There is no property
you can't sell, right?

184
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:31,832
If you'd like, do you want to go
have fun tonight?

185
00:10:32,199 --> 00:10:34,835
Let's go! Let's go to
our regular place, Chichin Pui Pui.

186
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,037
It's not about alcohol!

187
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:39,873
When you really
want to have fun, it's this!

188
00:10:41,108 --> 00:10:42,242
It's bowling!

189
00:10:42,309 --> 00:10:44,344
-Bowling?
-Let's go!

190
00:10:44,711 --> 00:10:45,545
We are going?

191
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:48,615
Good! We'll meet at 7:30!

192
00:10:48,682 --> 00:10:53,086
I'll make reservations. I'll finish up
my other tasks in the meantime.

193
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,688
See you!

194
00:10:56,056 --> 00:10:57,457
Are you really going?

195
00:10:57,958 --> 00:11:00,027
It's to sell a house!

196
00:11:00,961 --> 00:11:04,831
This is the bay window
that you said you have to have.

197
00:11:05,032 --> 00:11:06,867
Ah, this is it!

198
00:11:07,768 --> 00:11:12,005
She said she wants a life
where she waters plants

199
00:11:12,372 --> 00:11:14,641
every morning on the bay window.

200
00:11:15,575 --> 00:11:18,045
This window gets plenty of light.

201
00:11:18,211 --> 00:11:22,449
If you'd like, I will show
you this place again with your partner.

202
00:11:22,516 --> 00:11:25,085
No, I don't want it to sell before that,

203
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:28,255
so I'll apply today.

204
00:11:28,989 --> 00:11:29,990
Thank you very much.

205
00:11:30,724 --> 00:11:32,859
It will take time for the whole process,

206
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,795
so I have a favor to ask now.

207
00:11:35,228 --> 00:11:36,263
What would that be?

208
00:11:36,696 --> 00:11:39,866
I want to surprise
my girlfriend in this house,

209
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:42,803
so I would like you to open
the door just for that.

210
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,238
A surprise?

211
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,474
I want to stand by this bay window,

212
00:11:52,179 --> 00:11:53,580
to propose to her.

213
00:11:56,583 --> 00:12:02,556
So you're saying that your partner
doesn't know you are buying a house?

214
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:04,925
If she knew, it wouldn't be a surprise.

215
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:06,827
Right…

216
00:12:07,494 --> 00:12:10,097
But what would you do
in an unlikely event?

217
00:12:12,099 --> 00:12:12,966
An unlikely event?

218
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:13,867
How should I put it?

219
00:12:14,367 --> 00:12:18,972
In an unlikely event,
things don't go your way…

220
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:23,310
You are telling me that she won't
accept my proposal?

221
00:12:23,376 --> 00:12:25,145
No! That's not what I mean.

222
00:12:25,212 --> 00:12:26,346
Then what do you mean?

223
00:12:26,413 --> 00:12:30,917
You don't know if your partner
would like this house…

224
00:12:31,151 --> 00:12:33,086
You are the one
who recommended this house!

225
00:12:34,287 --> 00:12:38,458
Fine. I don't want to buy a precious house
from someone who thinks like that.

226
00:12:38,825 --> 00:12:40,260
I'll ask another realtor.

227
00:12:40,794 --> 00:12:43,897
Mr. Kamioka, please wait. Mr. Kamioka!

228
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:49,269
I am leaving now.

229
00:12:49,603 --> 00:12:51,571
Oh, you are early today.

230
00:12:52,639 --> 00:12:54,307
I guess I'll go home with you.

231
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:57,544
I can't go home with you.
I'm going bowling now.

232
00:12:57,944 --> 00:12:59,012
Bowling?

233
00:12:59,613 --> 00:13:02,482
Tonight's dinner's on the top right corner
of the fridge, as always.

234
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:05,418
Lately, the meals have been very standard,

235
00:13:05,485 --> 00:13:08,155
so I have an Ethiopian meal
prepared for you tonight.

236
00:13:08,221 --> 00:13:09,489
Ethiopian?

237
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:12,058
-Niwano!
-Yes!

238
00:13:13,393 --> 00:13:15,629
-Don't dawdle!
-Yes!

239
00:13:15,996 --> 00:13:17,297
-What?
-Goodbye.

240
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:20,700
You are bowling… with Niwano?

241
00:13:23,336 --> 00:13:25,872
Sangenya, you're gorgeous,
but you're not popular with men, huh?

242
00:13:26,273 --> 00:13:27,307
I am not.

243
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,544
Men don't like to feel inferior,

244
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:34,447
so when women are capable at work,
they question their own worth.

245
00:13:34,514 --> 00:13:36,149
I managed to get married though.

246
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:39,953
I'm sure Yashiro is not like that,

247
00:13:40,887 --> 00:13:42,622
but I don't know.

248
00:13:43,356 --> 00:13:44,958
Maybe he might be thinking
about it secretly.

249
00:13:45,292 --> 00:13:46,459
Do you think so?

250
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:51,164
My husband is not efficient
and is not valued at work,

251
00:13:51,865 --> 00:13:55,068
but he has no annoying pride,
and he is a great husband for me.

252
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:59,239
Does your husband have any requests
for the house you will buy?

253
00:13:59,606 --> 00:14:02,075
He won't say anything about my decisions.

254
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:03,944
The contract will be in my name as well.

255
00:14:04,277 --> 00:14:05,445
I see.

256
00:14:05,712 --> 00:14:06,947
Let's get started.

257
00:14:13,153 --> 00:14:14,721
This feels so good!

258
00:14:28,101 --> 00:14:29,502
It's your turn, Chief Sangenya.

259
00:14:38,712 --> 00:14:40,880
She said it's to sell a house,

260
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:43,416
but since Chief Sangenya agreed to come,

261
00:14:44,484 --> 00:14:46,553
she must be very good at bowling.

262
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:48,188
She's really confident.

263
00:14:49,656 --> 00:14:51,324
-Niwano!
-Yes!

264
00:14:53,193 --> 00:14:54,427
What's this hole for?

265
00:14:58,431 --> 00:15:00,934
Chief Sangenya, is this your
first time bowling?

266
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:02,068
It's my first time!

267
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:06,473
Wait!

268
00:15:25,525 --> 00:15:28,028
-Yeah!
-You are getting better!

269
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:35,835
SANGENYA

270
00:15:54,888 --> 00:15:57,924
This is my first time seeing someone
with a score of zero.

271
00:15:58,725 --> 00:16:00,493
It's actually sort of refreshing.

272
00:16:16,676 --> 00:16:17,577
What are you doing?

273
00:16:18,011 --> 00:16:21,848
Overtime. Work is
going to be my life from now on.

274
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:23,883
What happened?

275
00:16:29,189 --> 00:16:30,457
What is it?

276
00:16:31,624 --> 00:16:34,728
I… I…

277
00:16:36,162 --> 00:16:38,732
I was dumped.

278
00:16:39,632 --> 00:16:41,334
You got dumped?

279
00:16:41,401 --> 00:16:42,602
Didn't you say you don't date

280
00:16:42,669 --> 00:16:44,471
because you're the disinterested type?

281
00:16:44,537 --> 00:16:45,372
But…

282
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:49,109
I fell passionately in love
the night before last,

283
00:16:50,377 --> 00:16:52,245
and I confessed my love yesterday,

284
00:16:53,813 --> 00:16:57,550
and I got dumped by e-mail just now.

285
00:16:58,418 --> 00:16:59,786
That was fast.

286
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:06,292
Confessing your love the day
after you met him might be too soon.

287
00:17:06,793 --> 00:17:08,428
You say that,

288
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:13,800
but it was as if I caught a disease
where all I could about was him.

289
00:17:14,934 --> 00:17:17,804
I couldn't work, and I couldn't breathe.

290
00:17:18,338 --> 00:17:21,708
I thought I would die if I didn't
say anything.

291
00:17:22,609 --> 00:17:25,412
That's why I confessed to him.

292
00:17:26,579 --> 00:17:29,115
If you felt like dying, then it was good
that you confessed to him.

293
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:34,954
I did all I could.

294
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:41,194
From now on, I'll be independent
and live to work.

295
00:17:41,261 --> 00:17:43,463
I'll aim to be the legendary
genius office worker!

296
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:46,900
There is no phone call I cannot answer!

297
00:17:47,667 --> 00:17:51,571
I just want to lead a normal home life.

298
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:54,741
A wife doesn't come home every night,

299
00:17:54,808 --> 00:17:59,112
and her reason is to sell a house.
Isn't that strange?

300
00:17:59,379 --> 00:18:00,513
It is strange.

301
00:18:01,014 --> 00:18:03,883
While she's selling houses to others,
ours will collapse!

302
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:05,752
I feel sorry for you, Yashiro.

303
00:18:05,819 --> 00:18:11,458
It's a fact that she can't come home
since she's selling properties.

304
00:18:11,858 --> 00:18:14,594
But today, she went bowling with Niwano!

305
00:18:15,128 --> 00:18:17,330
Why didn't you go with them?

306
00:18:17,397 --> 00:18:18,598
She didn't invite me.

307
00:18:18,998 --> 00:18:19,899
I see.

308
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:24,537
I think I need that now for me
to make it through. Do the pui-pui.

309
00:18:24,804 --> 00:18:27,307
Oh, then I'll do
a special one for you today!

310
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:33,346
Chichin Pui-pui…

311
00:18:35,582 --> 00:18:37,517
Manager!

312
00:18:37,851 --> 00:18:41,054
Shirasu, you always have the worst timing!

313
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,423
I figured you would be here.

314
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:44,624
What is it?

315
00:18:44,691 --> 00:18:47,160
You were whining about
your divorce crisis to your wife

316
00:18:47,227 --> 00:18:49,062
who doesn't care about the family, right?

317
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:50,096
That's not it.

318
00:18:50,396 --> 00:18:54,133
Today, I brought a special guest
for you, Manager.

319
00:18:54,567 --> 00:18:55,502
What?

320
00:18:55,568 --> 00:18:59,239
An oasis for your dried up heart.

321
00:19:00,306 --> 00:19:01,407
Good evening.

322
00:19:02,542 --> 00:19:03,643
Ms. Misato.

323
00:19:09,549 --> 00:19:12,218
Thank you for the other day.

324
00:19:13,853 --> 00:19:14,854
What do you mean?

325
00:19:15,288 --> 00:19:17,991
You saved me from the cans of mackerel.

326
00:19:19,726 --> 00:19:20,627
That wasn't a big deal.

327
00:19:21,294 --> 00:19:23,563
It's a dirty place, but sit down.

328
00:19:24,597 --> 00:19:25,431
Thank you.

329
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:30,570
In any case, Manager's devil-wife,
house selling demon Sanchi,

330
00:19:31,004 --> 00:19:33,373
threatened me, abused me, rejected me,

331
00:19:33,873 --> 00:19:36,676
and hurt my feelings.

332
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:38,745
That's not it, Shirasu.

333
00:19:39,445 --> 00:19:44,217
She warned you to quit before
the company fired you.

334
00:19:44,284 --> 00:19:48,187
That's right. That's when Sanchi
saved this place too.

335
00:19:48,621 --> 00:19:51,758
But just because she can sell properties,

336
00:19:52,025 --> 00:19:54,227
she doesn't even say any
caring words to Manager.

337
00:19:54,594 --> 00:19:57,163
She makes him eat cold meals
all by himself.

338
00:19:57,230 --> 00:20:00,300
Isn't that the definition of a devil?

339
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:06,239
On the other hand, this Misato here
is kind and considerate.

340
00:20:06,306 --> 00:20:08,274
She's tall and very elegant.

341
00:20:08,641 --> 00:20:11,844
I think someone like Misato
is perfect for you.

342
00:20:11,911 --> 00:20:12,946
Ms. Shirasu…

343
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:16,316
Yashiro cares about his wife.

344
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:19,152
Yes, he loves his wife.

345
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:20,486
Kokoro.

346
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:24,324
But when your wife comes home
late every night…

347
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:26,092
you must be lonely.

348
00:20:26,693 --> 00:20:28,795
I'm used to it now.

349
00:20:29,629 --> 00:20:30,496
Here you go.

350
00:20:34,434 --> 00:20:36,035
-Hello.
-Welcome.

351
00:20:36,436 --> 00:20:39,405
Oh, this is Mika's new boss.

352
00:20:39,639 --> 00:20:40,473
Hello.

353
00:20:40,540 --> 00:20:41,908
Hello, I'm Niwano.

354
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:44,944
-How was bowling?
-Oh you know!

355
00:20:46,112 --> 00:20:47,413
Move!

356
00:20:48,982 --> 00:20:49,816
Manager,

357
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:51,484
please take a look at this.

358
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:52,785
Zero?

359
00:20:52,852 --> 00:20:55,521
It was Chief Sangenya's
first time bowling.

360
00:20:55,588 --> 00:20:57,590
She didn't know
there were holes in the ball.

361
00:20:57,824 --> 00:20:59,726
-What?
-You came to tell me that?

362
00:20:59,792 --> 00:21:01,861
Yes, I figured you'd be here.

363
00:21:02,962 --> 00:21:04,330
Niwano, I'm the man

364
00:21:04,631 --> 00:21:08,668
who came in second at a bowling
competition for our Shinjuku office.

365
00:21:09,235 --> 00:21:11,604
Why didn't you invite me?

366
00:21:12,705 --> 00:21:15,642
Second place? Who won first place, then?

367
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:17,977
That was…

368
00:21:21,848 --> 00:21:23,516
Me!

369
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:26,619
BOWLING COMPETITION,
WINNER, DYNAMITE MIKA

370
00:21:26,686 --> 00:21:27,553
No way!

371
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:30,890
I used to train to become
a professional bowler.

372
00:21:30,957 --> 00:21:34,560
My bowling name was Dynamite Mika.

373
00:21:34,827 --> 00:21:35,762
See?

374
00:21:36,496 --> 00:21:37,864
You're actually good at something?

375
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:39,732
-What did you say!
-Shut up!

376
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:44,270
Yashiro, now that the bowling is over,
your wife is probably home.

377
00:21:44,337 --> 00:21:46,506
Maybe she's waiting for you to come home.

378
00:21:48,508 --> 00:21:51,711
Why do I have to rush home, Kokoro?

379
00:21:52,378 --> 00:21:53,780
I'll just let her wait.

380
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:58,851
I'm a man who can go all night,
if I have to.

381
00:22:00,019 --> 00:22:05,091
In that case,
I might accompany you all night.

382
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:07,760
Here you go.

383
00:22:15,168 --> 00:22:17,770
I'm sorry. I'm coming in too.

384
00:22:22,175 --> 00:22:23,009
Go ahead.

385
00:22:23,976 --> 00:22:24,877
Thank you.

386
00:22:26,879 --> 00:22:30,283
Manager, those Ethiopian
dishes didn't suit you?

387
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:32,452
That's not the case.

388
00:22:33,252 --> 00:22:37,190
Last night, I got hungry, so I ate
ramen on my way home.

389
00:22:37,457 --> 00:22:39,892
You were out
drinking really late last night.

390
00:22:40,793 --> 00:22:43,596
Since you mention that, you are
the one who doesn't come home a lot.

391
00:22:44,263 --> 00:22:46,099
It's to sell a house!

392
00:22:46,399 --> 00:22:48,301
But you went bowling yesterday!

393
00:22:48,634 --> 00:22:50,436
It's to sell a house!

394
00:22:50,937 --> 00:22:55,041
I've never heard of a house being sold
because you went bowling.

395
00:22:56,375 --> 00:23:00,279
I thought of featuring properties
with photographs.

396
00:23:00,346 --> 00:23:01,748
What do you think of this?

397
00:23:02,982 --> 00:23:05,585
The biggest charm of this property
is the latest kitchen and bathroom.

398
00:23:05,651 --> 00:23:08,488
Women are particular around
those areas of the house.

399
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:14,861
Oh, but this has a kitchen and bath
on a different floor.

400
00:23:14,927 --> 00:23:20,399
This is really hard when bathing kids
and preparing meals at the same time.

401
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:22,435
I see.

402
00:23:22,969 --> 00:23:25,338
What about this property?

403
00:23:25,838 --> 00:23:29,375
It has stairs in the living room.
Will a family with kids like it too?

404
00:23:29,442 --> 00:23:31,711
This is not good at all!

405
00:23:31,778 --> 00:23:35,047
It's so dangerous! Kids may fall
down from between the stairs.

406
00:23:35,681 --> 00:23:38,384
Not everyone in this world
is raising kids.

407
00:23:39,152 --> 00:23:43,156
If you are going to deny my ideas,
then come up with your own too.

408
00:23:43,689 --> 00:23:46,592
Oh, I'm sorry. It's time to go!

409
00:23:46,959 --> 00:23:48,861
I'm leaving now.

410
00:23:50,129 --> 00:23:51,397
Good bye.

411
00:23:51,464 --> 00:23:53,466
Good bye.

412
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:57,303
Did you see that?
Oh she gets on my nerves!

413
00:23:57,770 --> 00:24:00,540
Does she think she's the busiest
person since she's a working mother?

414
00:24:01,107 --> 00:24:02,408
That was a bit…

415
00:24:02,842 --> 00:24:06,479
When I talk badly about mothers,
they make me the villain.

416
00:24:06,879 --> 00:24:08,481
My shoulders feel so tense now.

417
00:24:08,714 --> 00:24:12,485
To change things up, I'll show
you the property I picked out.

418
00:24:12,985 --> 00:24:14,487
You found something already?

419
00:24:14,554 --> 00:24:16,355
You sure are fast.

420
00:24:16,422 --> 00:24:19,625
I can show this property tomorrow morning.
Are you available?

421
00:24:19,926 --> 00:24:21,694
I'll go first thing in the morning.

422
00:24:22,128 --> 00:24:23,796
As you wish.

423
00:24:31,938 --> 00:24:35,107
Kenji, do you know
Ms. Sangenya's weak point?

424
00:24:39,011 --> 00:24:40,079
Do you know something?

425
00:24:40,746 --> 00:24:43,916
Ms. Sangenya sucks at bowling.

426
00:24:45,251 --> 00:24:47,053
She sucks at bowling?

427
00:24:48,354 --> 00:24:49,322
That's wonderful.

428
00:24:51,457 --> 00:24:55,928
Satoshi, why are you
telling me about Ms. Sangenya?

429
00:24:57,597 --> 00:24:58,564
Well…

430
00:24:59,398 --> 00:25:02,468
It's because you get happy
when I talk about her.

431
00:25:03,169 --> 00:25:04,403
Don't you see that?

432
00:25:04,937 --> 00:25:07,406
Do I really look that happy?

433
00:25:08,975 --> 00:25:12,445
Um, I'm just going to ask you directly.

434
00:25:13,913 --> 00:25:14,814
What?

435
00:25:16,849 --> 00:25:17,683
Kenji,

436
00:25:19,518 --> 00:25:21,220
do you like Sangenya?

437
00:25:26,559 --> 00:25:28,227
Oh, it's okay.

438
00:25:28,294 --> 00:25:29,462
I know.

439
00:25:30,529 --> 00:25:31,364
It's just…

440
00:25:32,732 --> 00:25:34,867
Even if that's the case…

441
00:25:36,936 --> 00:25:38,137
I think of you, Kenji…

442
00:25:42,508 --> 00:25:43,376
as…

443
00:25:44,043 --> 00:25:45,444
-As…?
-As…

444
00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:47,880
-As…?
-As…

445
00:25:48,414 --> 00:25:49,815
-As…?
-As…

446
00:25:51,817 --> 00:25:54,053
What is this? Wow!

447
00:25:55,454 --> 00:25:56,889
Satoshi, are you okay?

448
00:25:59,458 --> 00:26:01,594
You didn't hit your head? Let me see.

449
00:26:01,928 --> 00:26:02,762
Kenji!

450
00:26:05,097 --> 00:26:06,098
What's wrong?

451
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:10,169
Please let me stay like this for a while.

452
00:26:18,377 --> 00:26:19,211
I'm sorry.

453
00:26:19,779 --> 00:26:23,449
The fuse box is acting up,
and the lights turn off sometimes.

454
00:26:23,516 --> 00:26:26,919
Fix that already! It's not safe.

455
00:26:26,986 --> 00:26:29,622
I'm sorry. I'll ask
the management company right away.

456
00:26:35,695 --> 00:26:38,431
It's a condo, but it has a yard.
I like it.

457
00:26:38,864 --> 00:26:40,499
You sure are good, Ms. Sangenya.

458
00:26:40,566 --> 00:26:41,701
Thank you very much.

459
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:45,404
For me, this location is perfect.
I have nothing to say!

460
00:26:46,973 --> 00:26:48,140
Excuse me.

461
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:51,811
Hello?

462
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:55,081
I see. I got it.

463
00:26:56,482 --> 00:26:59,318
There's another client coming
here for a tour.

464
00:27:00,453 --> 00:27:02,722
If I don't decide quickly,
do you think it'll sell?

465
00:27:02,788 --> 00:27:05,157
I'm sorry to ask you so late.

466
00:27:05,224 --> 00:27:08,694
I wanted to see how the lighting
was at this time too.

467
00:27:08,761 --> 00:27:09,628
Oh? Someone is here.

468
00:27:11,497 --> 00:27:13,165
Ms. Asakura!

469
00:27:15,668 --> 00:27:19,505
I'm thinking of having
Ms. Asakura buy this home.

470
00:27:19,972 --> 00:27:24,076
I'm also thinking of having Ms. Usami
buy this home too.

471
00:27:25,011 --> 00:27:28,647
I came to see it yesterday
and I really like it.

472
00:27:28,914 --> 00:27:31,417
I feel fate here!

473
00:27:31,484 --> 00:27:34,320
I was about to apply just now too.

474
00:27:34,387 --> 00:27:39,525
But this layout here is for families
with kids.

475
00:27:40,026 --> 00:27:42,862
Is there any reason why you need
this place, Asakura?

476
00:27:43,295 --> 00:27:46,332
It's very close to my acupuncturist.

477
00:27:46,399 --> 00:27:47,933
Acupuncturist?

478
00:27:48,534 --> 00:27:53,039
This home has a room with shelves to
display my husband's plastic models.

479
00:27:53,339 --> 00:27:54,540
Plastic models?

480
00:27:54,607 --> 00:27:58,044
If that's the only silly reason,
then let me have this place.

481
00:27:58,110 --> 00:27:59,478
This is close to daycare,

482
00:27:59,545 --> 00:28:02,681
and I can shorten the time for
drop off and pick up by an hour.

483
00:28:02,748 --> 00:28:04,316
A silly reason?

484
00:28:04,817 --> 00:28:10,222
If I don't have Chen do acupuncture,
I get tight and I get migraines.

485
00:28:10,289 --> 00:28:13,159
-Chen?
-It's Mr. Chen, the acupuncturist.

486
00:28:13,225 --> 00:28:17,129
In that case, you can settle
for another property close by.

487
00:28:17,396 --> 00:28:20,733
This is on the ground level,
and I don't have to worry about noise.

488
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,636
It has no steps
and it's close to the park.

489
00:28:23,903 --> 00:28:26,305
It's like a home designed
for raising kids!

490
00:28:26,639 --> 00:28:28,407
-Um…
-You stay out of this!

491
00:28:29,675 --> 00:28:33,145
You keep talking about kids, but does
having a kid make you so important?

492
00:28:34,246 --> 00:28:39,318
I'm busy handling work that
is left undone by people like you.

493
00:28:39,685 --> 00:28:43,289
Maternity leave and reduced work hours
are our legal rights!

494
00:28:43,889 --> 00:28:47,359
To allow women to be able to work
and raise kids

495
00:28:47,426 --> 00:28:51,530
is a no-brainer for a member
of the Woman Project!

496
00:28:52,031 --> 00:28:55,968
Women who choose not to have kids
should be acknowledged more too.

497
00:28:56,435 --> 00:29:01,040
The idea that a woman's happiness is
dependent on childrearing is antiquated.

498
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:07,480
But maybe the taxes my kids will
pay will support you in the future.

499
00:29:07,546 --> 00:29:10,516
The Retirement fund's age requirement
is rising,

500
00:29:10,583 --> 00:29:12,918
and I don't even know if I could
receive it while I'm still alive.

501
00:29:12,985 --> 00:29:15,721
Decrease in the number of children
is a problem for all of Japan!

502
00:29:15,788 --> 00:29:19,492
In any case, stop talking
like you are right now!

503
00:29:19,558 --> 00:29:21,627
How I talk is not relevant!

504
00:29:21,694 --> 00:29:22,828
You're so annoying!

505
00:29:22,895 --> 00:29:24,730
-What!
-What?

506
00:29:25,364 --> 00:29:26,966
I have a suggestion.

507
00:29:27,867 --> 00:29:31,137
Let's be fair and have a drawing.

508
00:29:34,206 --> 00:29:36,208
A drawing? I don't agree with it.

509
00:29:36,509 --> 00:29:38,110
I have half a chance that I'll lose.

510
00:29:38,677 --> 00:29:40,379
You may think I'm childish,

511
00:29:40,846 --> 00:29:44,250
I can't bear the thought of losing
that home after everything she said.

512
00:29:44,316 --> 00:29:46,852
Don't worry. I took measures.

513
00:29:47,319 --> 00:29:48,387
What kind of measures?

514
00:29:55,995 --> 00:29:59,198
You can be quite sneaky, huh?

515
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:02,535
I've been through enough drama.

516
00:30:03,035 --> 00:30:04,503
I don't dislike people like you.

517
00:30:11,143 --> 00:30:13,479
We will start the drawing.

518
00:30:14,079 --> 00:30:16,115
Please do rock, paper, scissors first.

519
00:30:21,453 --> 00:30:22,621
Rock, paper, scissors.

520
00:30:23,088 --> 00:30:24,123
Yeah!

521
00:30:24,723 --> 00:30:28,060
Asakura, please pick either red or white.

522
00:30:28,994 --> 00:30:29,828
Red.

523
00:30:30,296 --> 00:30:33,632
Now, I'll put both red and white
into this thing.

524
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:36,001
If it's red, it's for Ms. Asakura,

525
00:30:36,569 --> 00:30:39,738
if it's white, then it's Ms. Usami.
Are you both fine with that?

526
00:30:46,645 --> 00:30:50,449
Now Ms. Usami, please go ahead
and turn this thing.

527
00:30:59,358 --> 00:31:00,993
-No way.
-Yes!

528
00:31:01,060 --> 00:31:04,063
Now Ms. Asakura earned the right
to purchase this property.

529
00:31:04,363 --> 00:31:05,497
The drawing is over.

530
00:31:06,932 --> 00:31:08,000
Please wait.

531
00:31:09,702 --> 00:31:12,805
Ms. Sangenya, you cheated.

532
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:16,508
How dare you?

533
00:31:16,575 --> 00:31:19,712
Chief Sangenya won't cheat!
You are making that up.

534
00:31:19,778 --> 00:31:21,080
You think so?

535
00:31:21,146 --> 00:31:22,448
Let's check then.

536
00:31:25,718 --> 00:31:27,686
See! It's red!

537
00:31:30,456 --> 00:31:32,191
-Red.
-I cheated.

538
00:31:34,293 --> 00:31:35,728
Why did you cheat?

539
00:31:36,462 --> 00:31:38,130
It's to sell a house.

540
00:31:39,231 --> 00:31:40,299
What?

541
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:47,039
Back in elementary school,
you were good at magic.

542
00:31:48,874 --> 00:31:50,409
She has a pigeon on her head.

543
00:31:50,476 --> 00:31:51,644
She was good at magic.

544
00:31:53,679 --> 00:31:55,614
Flags of all nations are
coming out of her mouth.

545
00:31:56,548 --> 00:32:02,788
Since there was fraud, I now have
the right to buy this house, right?

546
00:32:03,055 --> 00:32:06,725
Wait! I never asked her to cheat.

547
00:32:06,792 --> 00:32:10,829
Wait, please calm down,
you two. In a case like this…

548
00:32:13,666 --> 00:32:14,700
Well…

549
00:32:14,767 --> 00:32:16,335
What do you do in a case like this?

550
00:32:19,638 --> 00:32:20,739
I don't know.

551
00:32:20,806 --> 00:32:22,508
If you don't know,
then keep your mouth shut.

552
00:32:22,574 --> 00:32:23,442
I apologize.

553
00:32:25,077 --> 00:32:29,214
Then let me be in charge of
the next challenge.

554
00:32:30,582 --> 00:32:32,151
What are you going to do?

555
00:32:32,851 --> 00:32:36,055
How about a bowling match?

556
00:32:37,890 --> 00:32:39,391
Count me in!

557
00:32:40,993 --> 00:32:44,630
-What? No, I don't bowl!
-But…

558
00:32:45,264 --> 00:32:49,535
it will be Sangenya versus me.

559
00:32:53,605 --> 00:32:54,873
That's not good.

560
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:56,475
Mr. Rusudo, that's a bit…

561
00:32:56,542 --> 00:32:57,543
I'll take it.

562
00:32:59,244 --> 00:33:01,280
I don't think you should do that.

563
00:33:01,347 --> 00:33:04,550
There is no property I can't sell.

564
00:33:11,023 --> 00:33:13,625
Hello, this is Mika Shirasu!

565
00:33:13,959 --> 00:33:14,927
It's me.

566
00:33:19,932 --> 00:33:21,700
You will be transferred to voicemail

567
00:33:25,537 --> 00:33:27,072
You will be transferred to voicemail

568
00:33:30,676 --> 00:33:32,644
Stop it! What do you want!

569
00:33:33,512 --> 00:33:35,547
Mika Shirasu, I need your help.

570
00:33:41,487 --> 00:33:44,156
Dynamite Mika is here!

571
00:33:45,224 --> 00:33:49,027
Sangenya, are you ready for this?

572
00:33:51,163 --> 00:33:52,998
Say something!

573
00:34:01,573 --> 00:34:03,075
Yeah!

574
00:34:04,743 --> 00:34:06,111
You weren't watching?

575
00:34:08,514 --> 00:34:13,552
Swing your arm from front to back,

576
00:34:13,852 --> 00:34:16,622
release it on the fourth step.

577
00:34:20,793 --> 00:34:23,462
You can't even do
such a basic thing? You suck.

578
00:34:24,496 --> 00:34:25,597
Suck?

579
00:34:25,664 --> 00:34:28,901
It means you are not athletic.
Don't you even know that?

580
00:34:31,203 --> 00:34:32,471
Say something!

581
00:34:33,972 --> 00:34:38,177
Even if you could sell a house,
if you can't knock down a pin,

582
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:39,244
you are a loser!

583
00:34:39,678 --> 00:34:41,146
Focus!

584
00:34:46,919 --> 00:34:51,023
I don't know if you are
Sangenchaya or Ikejiriohashi,

585
00:34:51,790 --> 00:34:55,127
if you are not trying, go home already!

586
00:34:55,194 --> 00:34:57,196
-Not yet!
-Okay.

587
00:35:10,409 --> 00:35:13,078
I'm bowling right
now, so I won't be home tonight.

588
00:35:24,790 --> 00:35:29,127
Good evening, how about
some dinner if you are available?

589
00:35:29,561 --> 00:35:30,562
Misato.

590
00:35:34,233 --> 00:35:37,369
You must be busy.
Please don't worry about it.

591
00:35:51,450 --> 00:35:53,719
I WILL

592
00:35:58,457 --> 00:36:00,225
I WILL GO

593
00:36:07,266 --> 00:36:11,737
Let's leave already.
My right arm is dead now.

594
00:36:11,937 --> 00:36:13,171
Not yet!

595
00:36:13,705 --> 00:36:17,509
You have absolutely no talent,
you aren't athletic, it's a waste!

596
00:36:18,310 --> 00:36:20,746
Do whatever! Do as you wish!

597
00:36:32,457 --> 00:36:34,159
Oh! There she is.

598
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:36,595
Everyone, what's going on?

599
00:36:36,662 --> 00:36:39,898
I heard Sanchi's bowling is crazy and fun.

600
00:36:39,965 --> 00:36:42,100
We had to check it out.

601
00:36:42,167 --> 00:36:43,635
This is not a show.

602
00:36:43,702 --> 00:36:45,671
Oh, you are so protective.

603
00:36:45,737 --> 00:36:48,473
You never get to see a bowling game
with a house as a prize.

604
00:36:53,178 --> 00:36:54,713
Let's play.

605
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:56,348
Let's play.

606
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:02,654
It's starting.

607
00:37:07,793 --> 00:37:09,595
Chief Sangenya, stay calm!

608
00:37:11,630 --> 00:37:12,531
Sorry.

609
00:37:20,339 --> 00:37:21,473
She's wonderful.

610
00:37:21,540 --> 00:37:23,108
A miracle is not happening.

611
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:28,347
Go!

612
00:37:31,216 --> 00:37:32,050
She did it!

613
00:37:32,918 --> 00:37:34,086
Nice bowling!

614
00:37:35,887 --> 00:37:37,756
She sure is wonderful.

615
00:37:37,823 --> 00:37:39,691
How could she get a strike with that form?

616
00:37:39,758 --> 00:37:40,726
I wonder.

617
00:37:40,792 --> 00:37:42,861
Is it because of her "Go"?

618
00:37:42,928 --> 00:37:44,496
Was Sanchi really that bad?

619
00:37:44,563 --> 00:37:47,366
All she did was roll gutters until now.

620
00:37:57,709 --> 00:37:59,277
He's good.

621
00:38:21,033 --> 00:38:22,734
SANGENYA, RUSUDO

622
00:38:26,038 --> 00:38:28,073
One more throw and it'll be perfect.

623
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:30,542
She sure is Sanchi.

624
00:38:30,609 --> 00:38:32,844
What are you getting excited for?

625
00:38:33,412 --> 00:38:35,681
What happens if they are even?

626
00:38:37,082 --> 00:38:38,717
I wonder what will happen.

627
00:38:50,862 --> 00:38:51,830
Go!

628
00:38:53,165 --> 00:38:54,766
Go!

629
00:38:57,269 --> 00:38:58,136
Yes!

630
00:39:01,073 --> 00:39:04,476
Chief Sangenya, you haven't lost yet.

631
00:39:15,387 --> 00:39:17,622
The next throw will determine it all.

632
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:29,668
SANGENYA, RUSUDO

633
00:39:32,003 --> 00:39:35,707
He won! We won!

634
00:39:35,974 --> 00:39:39,144
We lost to Mr. Rusudo again.

635
00:39:39,478 --> 00:39:40,746
That was a good game.

636
00:39:41,646 --> 00:39:42,848
Should we get back to work?

637
00:39:43,682 --> 00:39:44,616
Yeah!

638
00:39:45,584 --> 00:39:48,954
So it's settled that
I will buy that place.

639
00:39:50,222 --> 00:39:51,156
No!

640
00:39:54,126 --> 00:39:56,461
Ms. Asakura will buy that place.

641
00:39:57,629 --> 00:39:58,697
What are you saying?

642
00:39:59,931 --> 00:40:01,333
Please take a look at this.

643
00:40:02,901 --> 00:40:03,835
What is this?

644
00:40:09,574 --> 00:40:11,009
It's a foul!

645
00:40:16,148 --> 00:40:18,683
Kenji Rusudo, 290 points.

646
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:21,153
Machi Sangenya, 299 points.

647
00:40:21,453 --> 00:40:22,821
I won!

648
00:40:23,388 --> 00:40:25,490
-Yeah!
-Way to go, Sangenya!

649
00:40:29,261 --> 00:40:33,832
I lost. It was a great game.
Thank you very much.

650
00:40:36,268 --> 00:40:38,637
What do you mean "a great game"?

651
00:40:39,671 --> 00:40:40,972
It was fun.

652
00:40:42,340 --> 00:40:44,309
Ms. Usami, it has been decided.

653
00:40:44,643 --> 00:40:46,678
Ms. Asakura, please fill out
the application form.

654
00:40:47,746 --> 00:40:48,680
Wait!

655
00:40:49,347 --> 00:40:53,485
It's just not right to lose to someone
who wants to live by her acupuncturist.

656
00:40:55,187 --> 00:41:00,258
I need that home to raise my children.

657
00:41:04,062 --> 00:41:05,030
What?

658
00:41:05,363 --> 00:41:09,301
You think everybody
gives in if you mention your kids?

659
00:41:10,335 --> 00:41:12,504
Ms. Sangenya, you only have work,
so you don't understand

660
00:41:12,571 --> 00:41:15,507
how hard it is to balance
work and raise kids.

661
00:41:15,574 --> 00:41:20,779
It is hard to do both, but if
you really want to do it, there is a way.

662
00:41:21,313 --> 00:41:23,915
You know you leave work at 16:00,
yet you set up

663
00:41:23,982 --> 00:41:26,751
a meeting at 15:30
knowing it won't end in 30 minutes,

664
00:41:26,818 --> 00:41:28,720
and you leave before the meeting ends.

665
00:41:29,287 --> 00:41:31,790
Are you telling me to ignore my kids?

666
00:41:32,324 --> 00:41:34,726
Are you saying it's fine for our
trust to be broken?

667
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,062
If you really want to work and raise kids,

668
00:41:37,128 --> 00:41:39,731
schedule meetings so that
you don't have to leave mid-way,

669
00:41:39,798 --> 00:41:42,868
or you need to explain ahead of time
that you only have 30 minutes.

670
00:41:43,201 --> 00:41:46,872
If you really want to balance both
work and kids, know your workload,

671
00:41:46,938 --> 00:41:49,541
and control how much work
you're capable of doing.

672
00:41:53,745 --> 00:41:56,748
That's not good! She'll sue for
maternity harassment.

673
00:41:56,815 --> 00:41:59,117
If you want to, go ahead and sue!

674
00:42:01,186 --> 00:42:03,321
Now, Ms. Asakura,
let's go over there to sign.

675
00:42:11,997 --> 00:42:13,932
MIRAINO OKA DAYCARE

676
00:42:13,999 --> 00:42:15,367
I'm so sorry.

677
00:42:15,634 --> 00:42:19,237
-Mommy, you are late!
-I'm sorry.

678
00:42:19,304 --> 00:42:23,008
Ms. Usami, I need you to come
and pick them up a little earlier.

679
00:42:23,074 --> 00:42:25,577
I'm sorry, a lot is going on right now.

680
00:42:26,378 --> 00:42:29,047
I'm hungry.

681
00:42:29,114 --> 00:42:31,950
I'm sorry. Let's put your shoes on.

682
00:42:32,651 --> 00:42:35,453
It's so like Rusudo to lose with a foul.

683
00:42:36,021 --> 00:42:38,990
Things seem complicated for women.

684
00:42:41,192 --> 00:42:42,894
It's complicated for men too.

685
00:42:44,496 --> 00:42:49,200
For us men, we have no exit route
when work doesn't go well.

686
00:42:50,001 --> 00:42:53,571
Women have a variation with their life,

687
00:42:54,372 --> 00:42:56,174
and I sort of admire that.

688
00:42:56,808 --> 00:42:58,677
A variation in life.

689
00:42:59,277 --> 00:43:02,280
It's hard to live when you only have
work to live for.

690
00:43:04,282 --> 00:43:06,918
I'm bored! I'm done being
a genius office worker!

691
00:43:10,355 --> 00:43:11,423
I'm going to the bathroom.

692
00:43:12,691 --> 00:43:13,591
Go ahead.

693
00:43:14,326 --> 00:43:18,563
Anyway, today's bowling match
was something.

694
00:43:18,630 --> 00:43:22,634
Mr. Fuse, please stop
such idiotic things from happening.

695
00:43:23,501 --> 00:43:25,136
You were no good, but you were a manager.

696
00:43:25,203 --> 00:43:27,839
No good? You don't have to be so harsh.

697
00:43:28,907 --> 00:43:34,846
Speaking of harsh, Sangenya just
shut that working mother up.

698
00:43:35,547 --> 00:43:39,884
I wonder how
Sangenya feels about her own child.

699
00:43:40,285 --> 00:43:45,223
I wonder if she empathizes with how
Asakura leads her life around work.

700
00:43:45,590 --> 00:43:47,158
Why don't you ask her?

701
00:43:47,592 --> 00:43:49,427
I can't ask her.

702
00:43:49,694 --> 00:43:51,563
What? You two are married.

703
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:53,665
It's like that, right? Mr. Fuse?

704
00:43:53,999 --> 00:43:55,533
Just ask her, you two are married.

705
00:43:55,867 --> 00:43:59,938
I can't ask her such a thing.

706
00:44:09,681 --> 00:44:11,616
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

707
00:44:11,683 --> 00:44:13,985
I thought about it yesterday,

708
00:44:14,352 --> 00:44:19,824
but I think it was just too
much for me to even do this project.

709
00:44:20,291 --> 00:44:23,862
I'm going to talk to my boss
and have me removed from this project.

710
00:44:24,129 --> 00:44:25,096
Is that so?

711
00:44:25,697 --> 00:44:28,700
Oh, but this is the Woman Project,

712
00:44:29,100 --> 00:44:32,737
so why not seek a way for you
to participate too.

713
00:44:34,706 --> 00:44:38,143
There is something I want to show you now.

714
00:44:40,178 --> 00:44:41,880
This open kitchen

715
00:44:41,946 --> 00:44:46,751
allows multiple people to work
together as a team,

716
00:44:46,818 --> 00:44:48,586
and get help with cooking and cleaning up.

717
00:44:50,688 --> 00:44:54,726
It has a yard, so you can have
a pool out there during the summer,

718
00:44:55,293 --> 00:44:59,731
and since it's not an apartment,
you don't have to worry about noise.

719
00:45:00,198 --> 00:45:01,399
Wait one second.

720
00:45:01,833 --> 00:45:04,736
Are you trying to get
me to buy this house?

721
00:45:04,803 --> 00:45:05,637
I am.

722
00:45:05,703 --> 00:45:09,874
This won't do at all.
It's very far from the daycare.

723
00:45:09,941 --> 00:45:13,311
Ms. Saki Usami, what is the Woman Project?

724
00:45:14,045 --> 00:45:15,780
What is it all of a sudden?

725
00:45:15,847 --> 00:45:17,182
-Niwano!
-Yes!

726
00:45:17,248 --> 00:45:19,350
What is the Woman Project?

727
00:45:19,651 --> 00:45:22,387
It's a project for
women to succeed and shine.

728
00:45:22,454 --> 00:45:24,823
What does it mean for the woman to shine?

729
00:45:24,889 --> 00:45:30,395
It means that women are happy
at work and at home.

730
00:45:30,962 --> 00:45:35,400
Men can continue to work whether
they shine or not.

731
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:39,437
On the other hand,
women are expected to shine.

732
00:45:40,271 --> 00:45:41,539
What does this mean?

733
00:45:43,441 --> 00:45:47,345
If it's a project to have women
succeed at home and at work,

734
00:45:47,412 --> 00:45:49,447
then it can just drop dead.

735
00:45:49,881 --> 00:45:53,885
This is your only life, there is no
need to follow other people's plans.

736
00:45:55,854 --> 00:46:00,558
This house is just three minutes'
walk from your husband's work.

737
00:46:01,693 --> 00:46:04,696
Your husband's company will have
a child care facility soon.

738
00:46:05,363 --> 00:46:09,100
You just let your husband
handle drop off and pick up.

739
00:46:09,801 --> 00:46:13,438
In addition, the road from this home
to your husband's work is very flat,

740
00:46:13,505 --> 00:46:16,407
so it's easy to push
the stroller to get to work.

741
00:46:16,908 --> 00:46:20,311
Ms. Saki Usami, it is impossible for you

742
00:46:20,378 --> 00:46:25,083
to do everything perfectly like your
mother who was a stay-at-home mom,

743
00:46:25,383 --> 00:46:26,718
since you have a job as well.

744
00:46:27,418 --> 00:46:29,921
Actually, it is strange that you are
the only one taking care

745
00:46:29,988 --> 00:46:34,125
of the household when you and your husband
are both working.

746
00:46:36,127 --> 00:46:39,731
From now on, men
should shine at work and at home.

747
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:46,671
Ms. Saki, you are shining already.

748
00:46:48,106 --> 00:46:48,940
I'm

749
00:46:50,808 --> 00:46:52,143
shining?

750
00:46:53,011 --> 00:46:56,848
Yes, you are shining to your max.

751
00:47:08,793 --> 00:47:11,596
I've already spoken to your husband
about it.

752
00:47:14,065 --> 00:47:15,900
-Saki.
-Honey.

753
00:47:17,869 --> 00:47:21,706
Your work is going to have a daycare?

754
00:47:23,608 --> 00:47:26,211
I didn't know, but I heard it is.

755
00:47:27,245 --> 00:47:29,681
You need to know stuff like that.

756
00:47:30,882 --> 00:47:31,950
I always thought…

757
00:47:33,418 --> 00:47:37,755
it would be better to leave you
in charge of our home.

758
00:47:38,423 --> 00:47:40,258
I didn't know you were so stressed.

759
00:47:41,759 --> 00:47:42,660
I'm sorry.

760
00:47:46,030 --> 00:47:48,266
Mr. Takahiro Usami and Mrs. Saki Usami,

761
00:47:49,067 --> 00:47:52,870
will you buy this home for ¥65 million?

762
00:47:57,408 --> 00:47:58,376
We'll buy it.

763
00:48:00,612 --> 00:48:01,512
I've got them.

764
00:48:08,219 --> 00:48:10,121
So-kun, don't follow me.

765
00:48:11,356 --> 00:48:13,391
It's like we have a new family member

766
00:48:14,025 --> 00:48:15,860
with that gift from Ms. Sangenya.

767
00:48:16,361 --> 00:48:18,296
Maybe kids won't be so bad.

768
00:48:18,363 --> 00:48:20,732
Raising kids is not that simple.

769
00:48:21,366 --> 00:48:22,867
I'm off!

770
00:48:24,469 --> 00:48:26,104
-Have a good day!
-See you later!

771
00:48:32,143 --> 00:48:33,478
Did something good happen?

772
00:48:35,113 --> 00:48:38,483
I fought with the one I love and I lost.

773
00:48:39,450 --> 00:48:41,719
I don't quite get it, but it's scary!

774
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:43,755
Hey, Kokoro.

775
00:48:44,756 --> 00:48:49,027
That thing you always do for Yashiro.
Can you do it to me too?

776
00:48:50,094 --> 00:48:52,263
"That thing"?

777
00:48:54,098 --> 00:48:55,033
You mean that?

778
00:48:55,466 --> 00:48:56,467
Yes.

779
00:48:58,770 --> 00:49:01,539
I don't have any customers,
so I guess it's fine!

780
00:49:01,606 --> 00:49:03,808
I'll do a special one for you.

781
00:49:04,742 --> 00:49:06,044
Please.

782
00:49:09,447 --> 00:49:14,018
Chichin pui-pui,

783
00:49:14,886 --> 00:49:17,922
pui, pui, pui!

784
00:49:23,861 --> 00:49:24,862
Okay!

785
00:49:25,363 --> 00:49:28,966
I think I can fight for love again.

786
00:49:30,034 --> 00:49:31,169
Thank you.

787
00:49:35,540 --> 00:49:38,209
THANK YOU FOR THE OTHER NIGHT
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO TONIGHT TOO. MISATO

788
00:49:48,319 --> 00:49:49,454
Welcome back.

789
00:49:50,621 --> 00:49:51,489
Manager!

790
00:49:51,556 --> 00:49:53,858
I sold the single family home
in Sendagaya to Ms. Usami.

791
00:49:54,325 --> 00:49:57,028
It wasn't Mr. Rusudo or Niwano. I sold it.

792
00:49:57,762 --> 00:49:58,596
Good job.

793
00:49:58,863 --> 00:50:00,164
I can go home early today.

794
00:50:00,865 --> 00:50:05,603
Oh, I see. I'm actually
meeting a friend today.

795
00:50:06,204 --> 00:50:08,373
You seem to come home late a lot lately.

796
00:50:09,407 --> 00:50:12,076
Is that a problem? I have things too.

797
00:50:13,311 --> 00:50:16,347
You should be the last one
to tell me about coming home late.

798
00:50:18,716 --> 00:50:19,617
Good job.

799
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:27,792
I will sell!

800
00:50:27,859 --> 00:50:29,660
-Dad!
-I'll be successful for sure!

801
00:50:29,727 --> 00:50:30,728
I can't push her away.

802
00:50:30,795 --> 00:50:32,797
I will help you achieve your dream.

803
00:50:32,864 --> 00:50:34,399
I won't sell the home my mother left me.

804
00:50:34,465 --> 00:50:35,400
MANAGER'S BETRAYAL

805
00:50:35,466 --> 00:50:36,868
He's cheating on you.

806
00:50:36,934 --> 00:50:38,569
Niwano! What is your job?

807
00:50:38,636 --> 00:50:40,471
Release the complex tie
of a father and a son!
